To build Neighborhood Tycoon (with rewarded ads, premium shops, social sharing, and invite rewards), 
you’ll need a game engine + supporting services. Here’s a clear breakdown of what apps/tools you can use to make this happen:

🛠️ Core Development Tools
🎮 Game Engine
Unity (recommended)

Best for mobile simulation/tycoon games.

Huge ecosystem of assets (shops, buildings, UI kits).

Easy integration with Google AdMob for rewarded ads.

Supports Android export directly to Play Store.

Unreal Engine (alternative)

More powerful graphics, but heavier for casual tycoon games.

Better suited if you want 3D realism.

Godot (lightweight option)

Open-source, free.

Good for 2D simulation games.

Smaller ecosystem compared to Unity.

📲 Backend & Cloud Services
Firebase (Google)

Authentication (player accounts).

Firestore database (store player progress, leaderboards).

Cloud Functions (event triggers, invite rewards).

Analytics (track retention, monetization).

PlayFab (Microsoft)

Tailored for games: leaderboards, events, player data.

Easy integration with Unity.

Supports in-app purchases and social features.

💰 Monetization
Google AdMob → Rewarded ads, interstitial ads, banners.

Google Play Billing Library → In-app purchases for premium shops, skins, event passes.

🌍 Social & Viral Features
Firebase Dynamic Links → Invite friends with referral rewards.

Unity Social Sharing Plugins → Share screenshots directly to WhatsApp, Instagram, TikTok.

🎨 Design & Assets
Figma → Wireframe and UI design.

Unity Asset Store → Buy ready-made shop/building models, decorations, and skins.

Blender → Create custom 3D models if you want unique shops.

🚀 Suggested Stack for You
Unity + Firebase + AdMob + PlayFab  
This combo gives you:

Smooth game development.

Easy monetization.

Scalable backend for leaderboards/events.

Viral features (sharing + invites).
